Pull_Quotes: I felt the last ten years, like all of my worries, all my- everything just sort of melt away and I was just so relaxed and I think that's been my... the most remarkable thing to me about this weekend: coming back and sort of remembering that feeling of knowing that I was in a safe place, that I could walk around with a beer, as silly as it is. But I don't have to worry. I could just be myself. I could be here. I could be very much in the moment and it was OK. And that feeling returning is really nice, and it's a neat memory for me to remember that feeling of having that place for four years.
